obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE FOREIGN TRADE (DEVELOPMENT AND REGULATION) ACT, 1992`
  line _________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line _________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `P OWER OF C ENTRAL G OVERNMENT TO MAKE O RDER AND ANNOUNCE FOREIGN TRADE POLICY`
  line `3. Powers to make provisions relating to imports and exports.`
  line `4. Continuance of existing orders.`
  line `5. Foreign Trade Policy.`
  line `6. Appointment of Director - General and his functions.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `I MPORTER - EXPORTER C ODE N UMBER AND LICENCE`
  line `7. Importer - exporter Code Number.`
  line `8. Suspension and cancellation of Importer - exporter Code Number.`
  line `9. Issue, suspension and cancellation of licence.`
  line `CHAPTER IIIA`
  line `Q UANTITATIVE RESTRICTIONS`
  line `9A. Power of Central Government to impose quantitative restrictions.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `S EARCH, SEIZURE, PENALTY AND CONFISCATION`
  line `10. Power relating to search and seizure.`
  line `11. Contravention of provisions of this Act, rules, orders and foreign trade policy.`
  line `11A. Crediting sums realised by way of penalties in Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line `11B. Empowering Settlement Commission for regularisation of export obligation default.`
  line `12. Penalty or confiscation not to interfere with other punishment.`
  line `13. Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `14. Giving of opportunity to the owner of the goods (including the goods connect ed with services or`
  line `technology), etc.`
  line `CHAPTER IVA`
  line `C ONTROLS ON EXPORT OF SPECIFIED GOODS, SERVICES AND TECHNOLOGY`
  line `14A. Controls on export of specified goods, services and technology.`
  line `14B. Transfer controls.`
  line `14C. Catch - all controls.`
  line `14D. Suspension or cancellation of a licence.`
  line `14E. Offences and penalties.`
