obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `THE FOREIGN TRADE (DEVELOPMENT AND REGULATION) ACT, 1992`
  line `A CT N O. 22 OF 1992`
  line `[7 th August, 1992.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the development and regulation of foreign trade by facilitating imports`
  line `into, and augmenting exports from, India and for matters connected therewith or incidental`
  line thereto.
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Forty - third Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Foreign Trade (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Act, 1992.`
  line `( 2 ) Sections 11 to 14 shall come into force at once and the remaining provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `deemed to have come into force on the 19th day of June, 1992.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Adjudicating Authority” means the authority specified in, or under, section 13;`
  line `( b ) “Appellate Authority” m eans the authority specified in, or under, sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line `( c ) “conveyance” means any vehicle, vessel, aircraft or any other means of transport including`
  line `any animal;`
  line `( d ) “Director General” means the Director General of Foreign Trade appointed under section 6;`
  line `1 [ ( e ) “import” and “export” means, —`
  line `( I ) in relation to goods, bringing into, or taking out of, India any goods by land, sea or air;`
  line `( II ) in relati on to services or technology, —`
  line `( i ) sup plying, services or technology —`
  line `( A ) from the territory of another count ry into the territory of India;`
  line `( B ) in the territory of another country to an Indian service consum er;`
  line `( C ) by a service supplier of another country, through commercial presence in India;`
  line `( D ) by a service supplier of another country, through presence of their natural`
  line `persons in India;`
  line `( ii ) supp lying, services or technology —`
  line `( A ) from India into the territory of any other country;`
  line `( B ) in India to the service consumer of any other country;`
  line `( C ) by a service suppli er of India, through commercial presence in the territory of any`
  line `other country;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 2, for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 2 7 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( D ) by a service supplier of India, through presence of Indian natural persons in the`
  line `territory of any other country:`
  line `Provided that “import” and “ export” in relation to the goods, services and technology regarding`
  line `Special Economic Zone or between two Special Economic Zones shall be governed in accordance`
  line `with the provisions contained in the Sp ecial Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005). ]`
  line `( f ) “ Importer - exporter Code Number” means the Code Number granted under section 7;`
  line `( g ) “licence” means a licence to import or export and includes a customs clearance permit and`
  line `any other permission issued or granted under this Act;`
  line `( h ) “Order” means any O rder made by the Central Government under section 3; and`
  line `( i ) “p rescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line `1 [ ( j ) “services” means service of any description which is made available to potential users and`
  line `includes all the tradable services specified under the General Agreement on Trade in Services entered`
  line `into amongst India and other countries who a re party to the said Agreement:`
  line `Provided that, this definition shall not a pply to the domain of taxation;`
  line `( k ) “service supplier” means any person who supplies a service and who intends to take benefit`
  line `under the foreign trade policy;`
  line `( l ) “specified goods or services or technology” means the goods or services or technology, the`
  line `export, import, transfer, re - transfer, transit and transshipment of which is prohibited or restricted`
  line `because of imposition of conditions on the grounds of their being pertinent or relevant to I ndia as a`
  line `Nuclear Weapon State, or to the national security of India, or to the furtherance of its foreign policy`
  line `or its international obligations under any bilateral, multil ateral or international treaty, co venant,`
  line `convention or arrangement relating to weapons of mass destruction or their means of delivery to`
  line `which India is a party or its agreement with a foreign country under the foreign trade policy`
  line `formulated and notif ied under section 5 of the Act;`
  line `( m ) “technology” means any information (including information embodied in software), other`
  line `than information in the public domain, that is capable of being used in —`
  line `( i ) the development, production o r use of any goods or software;`
  line `( ii ) the development of, or the carrying out of, an industrial or commercial activity or the`
  line `pr ovision of service of any kind.`
  line `Explanation. — F or the purpose of this clause —`
  line `( a ) when technology is described wholly or partly by reference to the uses to which it (or the`
  line `goods to which it relates) may be put, it shall include services which are provided or used, or`
  line `which are capable of being used in the developm ent, production or use of such technology or`
  line goods;
  line `( b ) “public domain” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( i ) of section 4 of`
  line `the Weapons of Mass Destruction and their Delivery System (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities)`
  line `Act, 2005 (21 of 2005). ]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `P OWER OF C ENTRAL G OVERNMENT TO MAKE O RDER AND ANNOUNCE 2 [FOREIGN TRADE POLICY]`
  line `3. Powers to make provision s relating to imports and exports. — ( 1 ) The Central Government`
  line `may, by Order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for the development and regulation of`
  line `foreign trade by facilitating imports and increasing exports.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “EXPORT AND IMPORT POLICY” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may also, by Order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for`
  line `prohibiting, restricting or otherwise regulating, in all cases or in specified classes of cases and subject to`
  line `such ex c eptions, if any, as may be made by or under the Order, the 1 [ import or export of goods or services`
  line `or technology]:`
  line `2 [ Provided that the provisions of this sub - section shall be applicable, in case of import or export of`
  line `services or technology, only when the service or technology provider is availing benefit s under the`
  line `foreign trade policy or is dealing with specified ser vices or specified technologies. ]`
  line `( 3 ) All goods to which any Order under sub - section ( 2 ) applies shall be deemed to be goods the`
  line `import or export of which has been prohibited under section 11 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962)`
  line `and all the provisions of that Act shall have effect accordingly.`
  line `2 [ ( 4 ) W ithout prejudice to anything contained in any other law, rule, regulation, notification or order,`
  line `no permit or licence shall be necessary for import or export of any goods, nor any goods shall be`
  line `prohibited for import or export except, as may be required under this Act, or rules or orders made`
  line thereunder.]
  line `4. Continuance of existing orders. — All Orders made under the Imports and Exports (Control) Act,`
  line `1947 (18 of 1947), and in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall, so far as they are`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue to be in force and shall be deemed to have been`
  line `made under this Act.`
  line `3 [ 5. Foreign Trade Policy. — The Central Government may, from time to time, formulate and`
  line `announce, by notification in the Official Gazette, the foreign t rade policy and may also, in like manner,`
  line `amend that policy:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may direct that, in respect of the Special Economic Zones, the`
  line `foreign trade policy shall apply to the goods, services and technology with such exceptions, modifications`
  line `and adaptations, as may be specified by it by notifi cation in the Official Gazette. ]`
  line `6. Appointment of Dir ector General and his functions. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may appoint`
  line `any person to be the Director General of Foreign Trade for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Director General shall advise the Central Gover nment in the formulation of the 4 [foreign trade`
  line `policy] and shall be responsible for carrying out that policy.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may, by Order published in the Official Gazette, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by it under this Act (other than the powers under sections 3, 5, 15, 16 and 19) may also be`
  line `exercised, in such cases and subject to such conditions, by the Director - General or such other officer`
  line `subordinate to the Director General, as may be specified in the Order.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `I MPORTER - EXPORTER C ODE N UMBER AND LICENCE`
  line `7. Impo rter - exporter Code Number. — No person shall make any import or export except under an`
  line `Importer - exporter Code Number granted by the Director General or the officer authorised by the Director`
  line `General in this behalf, in accordance with the procedure specified in this behalf by the Director General:`
  line `5 [ Provided that in case of import or export of services or technology, the Importer - exporter Code`
  line `Number shall be necessary only when the service or technology provider is taking benefit s under the`
  line `foreign trade policy or is dealing with specified ser vices or specified technologies. ]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 4, for “imp ort or export of goods” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 5 (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “export and import policy” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `8. Suspension and cancellation o f Importer - exporter Code Number. — 1 [ ( 1 ) Where —`
  line `( a ) any person has contravened any of the provisions of this Act or any rules or orders made`
  line `thereunder or the foreign trade policy or any other law for the time being in force relating to Central`
  line `excise or customs or foreign exchange or has committed any other economic offence under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force as may be specified by the Central Government by notificat ion in the`
  line `Official Gazette; or`
  line `( b ) the Director Gener al or any other officer authoris ed by him has reason to believe that any`
  line `person has made an export or import in a manner prejudicial to the trade relations of India with any`
  line `foreign country or to the interests of other persons engaged in imports or exports or has brought`
  line `disrepute to the credit or the goods of, or services or technology provid ed from, the country; or`
  line `( c ) any person who imports or exports specified goods or services or technology, in contravention`
  line `of any provision of this Act or any rules or orders made thereund er or the foreign trade policy,`
  line `the Director Gener al or any other officer authoris ed by him may call for the record or any other`
  line `information from that person and may, after giving to that person a notice in writing informing him of the`
  line `grounds on which it is proposed to suspend or cancel the Importer - exporter Code Number and after giving`
  line `him a reasonable opportunity of making a representation in writing within such reasonable time as may be`
  line `specified in the notice and, if that person so desires, of being heard, suspend for a period, as may be`
  line `specified in the order, or cancel the Importer - exporter Code Number granted to that person.]`
  line `( 2 ) W here any Importer - exporter Code Number granted to a person has been suspended or cancelled`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ), that person shall not be entitled to 2 [ import or export any g oods or services or`
  line `technology] except under a special licence, granted, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may`
  line `be prescribed, by the Director General to that person.`
  line `9. Issue, suspension and cancellation of licence. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may levy fees,`
  line `subject to such exceptions, in respect of such person or class of persons making an application for`
  line `3 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] of in respect of any`
  line `3 [licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing financial or fiscal benefits] granted or renewed in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) The Directo r General or an officer authoris ed by him may, on an application and after making`
  line `such inquiry as he may think fit, grant or renew or refuse to grant or renew a licence to import or export`
  line `such class or classes of goods or services or technology as may be prescribed and, grant or renew or`
  line `refuse to grant or renew a certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing financial or fiscal benefit, after`
  line `recording in writing his reasons for such refusal.]`
  line `( 3 ) A 3 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] granted or`
  line `re newed under this section shall —`
  line `( a ) be in such form as may be prescribed;`
  line `( b ) be valid for such period as may be specified therein; and`
  line `( c ) be subject to such terms, conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed or as specified in the`
  line `3 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] with reference to`
  line `the terms, conditions and restrictions so prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) The Director - General or the officer authorised under sub - section ( 2 ) may, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, for good and sufficient reasons, to be recorded in writing, suspend or`
  line `cancel any 3 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] granted`
  line `under this Act:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 8, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “import or export any goods” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for “licence” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `Provided that no such suspension or cancellation shall be made except after giving the holder of the`
  line `1 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 5 ) An appeal against an order refusing to grant, or renew or suspending or cancelling, a 1 [ licence,`
  line `certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowin g financial or fiscal benefits] shall lie in like manner as an`
  line `appeal against an order would lie under section 15.`
  line `2 [CHAPTER IIIA`
  line `Q UANTITATIVE RESTRICTIONS`
  line `9A. Power of Central Government to impose quantitative restrictions. — ( 1 ) If the Central`
  line `Government, after conducting such enquiry as it deems fit, is satisfied that any goods are imported into`
  line `India in such increased quantities and under such conditions as to cause or threaten to cause serious injury`
  line `to domestic industry, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, impose such quantitative restrictions`
  line `on the import of such goods as it may deem fit:`
  line `Provided that no such quantitative restrictions shall be imposed on any goods originating from a`
  line `developing country so long as the share of imports of such goods from that country does not exceed three`
  line `per cent. or where such goods originate from more than one developing country, then, so long as the`
  line `aggregate of the imports from all such countries taken together does not exceed nine per cent. of the total`
  line `impor ts of such goods into India.`
  line `( 2 ) The quantitative restrictions imposed under this section shall, unless revoked earlier, cease to have`
  line `effect on the expiry of four years fr om the date of such imposition:`
  line `Provided that if the C entral G overnment is of the opinion that the domestic industry has taken`
  line `measures to adjust to such injury or threat thereof and it is necessary that the quantitative restriction s`
  line `should contin ue to be imposed to prevent such injury or threat and to facilitate the adjustments, it may`
  line `extend the said period beyond four years:`
  line `Provided further that in no case the quantitative restriction s s hall continue to be imposed beyond a`
  line `period of ten years from the date on which such restriction s were first imposed.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may, by rules provide for the manner in which goods, the import of`
  line `which shall be subject to quantitative restrictions under this section, may be identified and the manner in`
  line `which the causes of serious injury or causes of threat of serious injury in relation t o such goods may be`
  line determined.
  line `( 4 ) Fo r the purposes of this section —`
  line `( a ) “developing country” means a country notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line `Gazett e, in this regard;`
  line `( b ) “domestic industry” means the producers of goods (including pr oducers of agricultural`
  line `goods) —`
  line `( i ) a s a whole of the like goods or directly competitive goods in India; or`
  line `( ii ) w hose collective output of the like goods or directly competitive goods in India`
  line `constitutes a major share of the total product ion of the said goods in India;`
  line `( c ) “serious injury” means an injury causing significant overall impairment in the p osition of a`
  line `domestic industry;`
  line `( d ) “threat of serious injury” means a clear and immi nent danger of serious injury.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 9, for “licence” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `S EARCH, SEIZURE, PENALTY AND CONFISCATION`
  line `10. Power relating to search and seizure. — 1 [( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification i n`
  line `the Official Gazette, authoris e any person for the purposes of exercisi ng such powers with respect to, —`
  line `( a ) entering such premises where the goods are kept, stored or processed, manufactured, traded or`
  line `supplied or received for the purposes of import or export and searching, inspecting and seizing of`
  line `such goods, documents, things and conveyances connected with such import and export of goods;`
  line `( b ) entering such premises from which the services or technology are being provided, suppli ed,`
  line `received, consumed or utilis ed and searching, inspecting and seizing of such goods, documents,`
  line `things and conveyances connected with such import and exp ort of services and technology,`
  line `s ubject to su ch requirements and conditions and with the approval of such officer, as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of c lause ( b ) shall be a pplicable, in case of import or export of services`
  line `or technology, only when the service or technology provider is availing benefit under the foreign trade`
  line `policy or is dealing with specified ser vices or specified technologies. ]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall, so far as may be, apply to every search and seizure made under this section.`
  line `2 [ 11. Contravention of provisions of this Act, rules, orde rs and foreign trade policy. — ( 1 ) No`
  line `export or import shall be made by any person except in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `rules and orders made there under and the foreign trade policy for the time being in force.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person makes or abets or attempts to make any export or import in contravention of`
  line `any provision of this Act or any rules or orders made there under or the foreign trade policy, he shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of not less than ten thousand rupees and not more than five times the value of the goods`
  line `or services or technology in respect of which any contravention is made or attempted to be made,`
  line `whic hever is more.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any person signs or uses, or causes to be made, signed or used, any declaration, statement`
  line `or document submitted to the Director General or any officer authorised by him under this Act, knowing`
  line `or having reason to believe that such declaration, state ment or document is forged or ta mpered with or`
  line `false in any material particular, he shall be liable to a penalty of not less than ten thousand rupees or more`
  line `than five times the val ue of the g oods or services or technology in respect of which such declaration,`
  line `statement or document had bee n submitted, whichever is more.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any per son, on a notice to him by the A djudicating Authority, admits any contravention,`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority may, in such class or classes or cases and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, determine, by way of settlement, an a mount to be paid by that person.`
  line `( 5 ) A penalty imposed under t his Act may, if it is not paid by any person, be recovered by any one or`
  line `more o f the following modes, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the Director General may deduct or require any officer subordinate to him to deduct the`
  line `amount payable under this Act from any money owing to such person which may be under the control`
  line `of such officer; or`
  line `( b ) the Director General may require any officer of customs to deduct the amount payable under`
  line `this Act from any money owing to such person which may be under the control of such officer of`
  line `customs, as if the said amount is payable under the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962); or`
  line `( c ) the Director General may require the Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or any other officer of Customs to recover the amount so payable by`
  line `detaining or selling any goods (including the goods connected with services or technology) belonging`
  line `to such person which are under the control of the Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 11, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 11 (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
