  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `Commissioner or Customs or any other officer of Customs, as if the said amount is payable under the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962); or`
  line `( d ) if the amount cannot be recovered from such person in the manner provide d in clauses ( a ), ( b )`
  line `and ( c ), —`
  line `( i ) the Director General or any officer authoris ed by him may prepare a certificate signed by`
  line `him specifying the amount due from such person and send it to the Collector of the District in`
  line `which such person owns any property or resides or carries on business and the said Collector on`
  line `receipt of such certificate shall proceed to recover from such person the amount specified`
  line `thereunder as if it wer e an arrear of land revenue; or`
  line `( ii ) the Director General or any officer authorised by him (including an officer of Customs`
  line `who shall then exercise his powers under the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) ) and in accordance`
  line `with the rules made in this behalf, detain any movable or immovable property belonging to or`
  line `under the control of such person, and detain the same until the amount payable is paid, as if the`
  line `said amount is payable under the Customs Act, 1962; and in case, any part of the said amount`
  line `payable or of the cost of the distress or keeping of the property, remains unpaid for a period of`
  line `thirty days next after any such distress, may cause the said property to be sold and with the`
  line `proceeds of such sale, may satisfy the amount payable and costs including cost of sale remaining`
  line `unpaid and shall render the surplus, if any to such person.`
  line `( 6 ) W here the terms of any bond or other instrument executed under this Act or any rules made`
  line `thereunder provide that any amount due under such instrument may be recovered in the manner laid down`
  line `in sub - section ( 5 ), the amount may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery, be recovered in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of that sub - section.`
  line `( 7 ) W ithout prejudice to the provis i o n s containe d in this section, the Importer - Exporter Code Number`
  line `of any person who fails to pay any penalty imposed under this Act, may be suspended by the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority till the penalty is paid or recovered, as the case may be.`
  line `( 8 ) Where any contravention of any provision of this Act or any rules or orders made thereunder or`
  line `the foreign trade policy has been, is being, or is attempted to be, made, the goods (including the goods`
  line `connected with services or technology) together with any package, covering or receptacle and any`
  line `conveyances shall, subject to such conditions and requirement as may be prescribed, be liable to`
  line `confisca tion by the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `( 9 ) The goods (including the goods connected with services o r technology) or the conveyance`
  line `confiscated under sub - section ( 8 ) may be released by the Adjudicating Authority, in such manner and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, on payment by the person concerned of the redemption`
  line `charges equivalent to the market value of the goods or conveyance, as the case may be.]`
  line `1 [ 11A. Crediting sums realised by way of penalties in Consolidated Fund of India. — All sums`
  line `realis ed by way of penalties under this Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line `11B. Empowering Settlement Commission for regularisation of export obligation default. —`
  line `Settlement of customs duty and interest thereon as ordered by the Settlement Commission as constituted`
  line `under section 32 of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), shall be deemed to be a settlement under`
  line `this Act.]`
  line `12. Penalty or confiscation not to i nterfere with other punishments. — No penalty imposed or`
  line `confiscation made under this Act shall prevent the imposition of any other punishment to which the`
  line `person affected thereby is liable under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `13. Adjudicating Authority. — Any penalty may be imposed or any confiscation may be adjudged`
  line `under this Act by the Director General or, subject to such limits as may be specified, by such other officer`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazett e, authorise in this behalf.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 13 (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
