obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `14. Giving of opportunity to the owner of the 1 [goods (including the goods connected with`
  line `services or technology)], etc. — No order imposing a penalty or of adjudication of confiscation shall be`
  line `made unless the owner of the 1 [ goods (including the goods connected with services or technology)] or`
  line `conveyance, or other person concerned, has been given a notice in writing —`
  line `( a ) informing him of the grounds on which it is proposed to impose a penalty or to confiscate`
  line `such 1 [goods (including the goods connected with services or technology)] or conveyance; and`
  line `( b ) to make a representation in writing within such reasonable time as may be specified in the`
  line `notice against the imposition of penalty or confiscation mentione d therein, and, if he so desires, of`
  line `being heard in the matter.`
  line `2 [ CHAPTER IVA`
  line `C ONTROLS ON EXPORT OF SPECIFIED GOODS, SERVICES AND TECHNOLOGY`
  line `14A. Controls on export of specified goods, services and technology. — ( 1 ) In regard to controls on`
  line `export of specified goods, services and technology referred to in this C hapter, the Weapons of Mass`
  line `Destruction and their Delivery Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities) Act, 2005 (21 of 2005) shall`
  line `apply to exports, transfers, re - trans fers, brought in transit, trans - shipment of, and brokering in specified`
  line `goods, technology or services.`
  line `( 2 ) All terms, expressions or provisions of the Weapons of Mass Destruction and their Delivery`
  line `Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities) Act, 2005 (21 of 2005) shall apply to the specified goods,`
  line `services or technology with such exceptions, modifications and adaptations as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government by notifi cation in the Official Gazette.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct th at any of the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter —`
  line `( a ) s hall not apply to any good s, services or technologies, or`
  line `( b ) s hall apply to any goods, services or technologies with such exceptions, modifications and`
  line `adaptations as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `14B. Transfer controls. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules in conformity with the provisions of the Weapons of Mass Destruction and their Delivery`
  line `Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities) Act, 2005 (21 of 2005) for, or, in connection with, the`
  line `imposition of controls in relation to transfer of specified goods, services or technology.`
  line `( 2 ) No goods, services or technology notified under this Chapter shall be exported, transferred,`
  line `re - transferred, brought in transit or transshipped except in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Weapons of Mass Destruction and their Delivery Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities) Act, 2005`
  line `(21 of 2005) or any other relevant Act.`
  line `14C. Catch - all controls. — No person shall export any material, equipment or technology knowing`
  line `that such material, equipment or technology is intended to be used in the design or manufacture of a`
  line `biological weapon, chemical weapon, nuclear weapon or other nuclear explosive device, or in their`
  line `missile delivery systems.`
  line `14D. Suspension or cancellation of a licence. — The Directo r General or an officer authoris ed by`
  line `him may, by order, suspend or cancel a licence to import or export of specified goods or services or`
  line `technology without giving the holder of the licenc e a reasonable opportunity of being heard but such`
  line `person shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard within six months of such order and`
  line `thereup on the Director General or the officer so authoris ed may, if necessary, by order in writing,`
  line `confir m, modify or revoke such order.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 14, for “goods” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Ins. b y s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `14E. Offences and penalties. — ( 1 ) In case of a contravention relating to specified goods, services or`
  line `tec hnologies, the penalty shall be in accordance with the provisions of the Weapons of Mass Destruction`
  line `and their Delivery Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful Activities) Act, 2005 (21 of 2005).`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets, any of the provision(s) of this`
  line `Chapter in relation to import or export of any specified goods or services or technology, he shall, without`
  line `prejudice to any penalty which may be imposed on him, be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `stipulated in the Weapons of Mass Destruction and their Delivery Systems (Prohibition of Unlawful`
  line `Activities) Act, 2005 (21 of 2005).`
  line `( 3 ) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Chapter without the previous`
  line `sanction of the Central Go vernment or any officer authoris ed in this behalf by the Central Governme nt by`
  line `general or special order.]`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `A PPEAL AND 1 [REVIEW]`
  line `15. Appeal. — ( 1 ) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order made by the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under this Act may prefer an appeal, —`
  line `( a ) where the decision or order has been made by the Director Gene ral, to the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( b ) where the decision or order has been made by an officer subordinate to the Director General,`
  line `to the Director General or to any officer superior to the Adjudicating Authority authorised by the`
  line `Direc tor General to hear the appeal,`
  line `within a period of forty - five days from the date on which the decision or order is served on such person:`
  line `Provided that the Appellate Authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the aforesaid period, allow such appeal to be preferred`
  line `within a further period of thirty days:`
  line `Provided further that in the case of an appeal against a decision or order imposing a penalty or`
  line `redemption charges, no such appeal shall be entertained unless the amount of penalty or redemption`
  line `charges has been deposited by the appellant:`
  line `Provided also that, where the Appellate Authority is of opinion that the deposit to be made will cause`
  line `undue hardship to the appellant, it may, at its discretion, dispense with such deposit either unconditionally`
  line `or subject to such conditions as it may impose.`
  line `( 2 ) The Appellate Authority may, after giving to the appellant a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard, if he so desires, and after making such further inquiries, if any, as it may consider necessary, make`
  line `such orders as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or reversing the decision or order appealed against, or`
  line `may send back the case with such directions, as it may think fit, for a fresh adjudicatio n or decision, as the`
  line `case may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary:`
  line `Provided that an order enhancing or imposing a penalty or redemption charges or confiscating 2 [the`
  line `goods (including the goods connected with services or technology ) ] of a greater value shall not be made`
  line `under this section unless the appellant has been given an opportunity of making a representation, and, if`
  line `he so desires, of being heard in his defence.`
  line `( 3 ) The order made in appeal by the Appellate Authority shall be final.`
  line `3 [ 16. Review. — The Central Government, in the case of any decision or order made by the Director`
  line `General, or the Director General in the case of any decision or order made by any officer subordinate to`
  line `him, may on its or his own motion or otherwise, call for and examine the records of any proceeding, for`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 16, for “REVISION” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for “goods” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for section 16 ( w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
