  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `the purpose of satisfying itself or himself, as the case may be, as to the correctness, legality or propriety of`
  line `such decision or order and make such orders thereo n as may be deemed fit:`
  line `Provided that no decision or order shall be varied under this section so as to prejudicially affect any`
  line `person unless such person —`
  line `( a ) has, within a period of two years from the date of such decision or o rder, received a notice to`
  line `show cause why such decision or order shall not be varied; and`
  line `( b ) has been given a reasonable opportunity of making representation and, if he so desires, of`
  line `being heard in his defence.]`
  line `17. Powers of Adjudicating and other Authorities. — ( 1 ) Every authority making any adjudication`
  line `or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of 1 [ r eview ] under this Act shall have all the powers of a`
  line `civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line `( b ) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line `( c ) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line `( d ) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line `( 2 ) Every authority making any adjudication or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of`
  line `1 [ r eview ] under this Act shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedu re, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line `( 3 ) Every authority making any adjudication or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of`
  line `1 [ r eview ] under this Act shall have the power to make such orders of an interim nature as it may think fit`
  line `and may also, for sufficient cause, order the stay of operation of any decision or order.`
  line `( 4 ) Clerical or arithmetical mistakes in any decision or order or errors arising therein from any`
  line `accidental slip or omission may at any time be corrected by the authority by which the decision or order`
  line `was made, either on its own motion or on the application of any of the parties:`
  line `Provide d that where any correction proposed to be made under this sub - section will have the effect of`
  line `prejudicially affecting any person, no such correction shall be made except after giving to that person a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of making a representation in the matter and no such correction shall be made`
  line `after the expiry of two years from the date on which such decision or order was made.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `18. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No order made or deemed to have been made under`
  line `this Act shall be called in question in any court, and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or any order`
  line `made or d eemed to have been made thereunder.`
  line `2 [18A. Application of other laws not barred. — The provision s of this Act shall be in addition to,`
  line `and not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law fo r the time being in force.]`
  line `19. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2010, s. 19, for “Revision” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
