  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which a special licence may be issued under`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) of section 8;`
  line `( b ) the exceptions subject to which and the person or class of persons in respect of whom fees`
  line `may be l evied and the manner in which a 1 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing`
  line `financial or fiscal benefits ] may be granted or renewed under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `2 [( c ) the class or classes of goods (including the goods connected with service or technology) for`
  line `which a licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing financial or fiscal benefits may be`
  line `granted under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 9; ]`
  line `( d ) the form in which and the terms, conditions and restrictions subject to which 1 [ licence,`
  line `certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing financial or fiscal benefits ] may be granted under`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) of section 9;`
  line `( e ) the conditions subject to which a 1 [ licence, certificate, scrip or any instrument bestowing`
  line `financial or fiscal benefits ] may be suspended or cancelled under sub - section ( 4 ) of section 9;`
  line `3 [( ea ) the matter in which goods the import of which shall be subject to quantitative restrictions,`
  line `may be identified and the manner in which the causes of serious injury or causes of threat of serious`
  line `injury in relation to such goods may be determined under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 9A;]`
  line `( f ) the premises, 4 [ goods (including the goods connected with the service or technology) ],`
  line `documents, things and conveyances in respect of which and the requirements and conditions subject`
  line `to which power of entry, search, inspection and seizure may be exercised under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line `( g ) the class or classes of cases for which and the manner in which an amount, by way of`
  line `settlemen t, may be determined under 5 [ sub - section ( 4 ) of section 11 ];`
  line `6 [( h ) the requirement s and co nditions subject to which goods ( including the goods connected with`
  line `the service or technology ) and conveyances shall be liable to confiscation under sub - section ( 8 ) of`
  line `section 11;]`
  line `7 [( i ) the manner in which and the co nditions subject to which goods ( including the goods`
  line `connected with the service or technology ) and conveyances may be released on payment of`
  line `redemption charges under sub - section ( 9 ) of section 11;]`
  line `( j ) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be, or may be, made by rules.`
  line `( 3 ) Every rule and every Order made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each H ouse of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or the Order or both Houses agree that the rule or the`
  line `Order should not be made, the rule or the Order, as the case may be, shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or the`
  line Order.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 201 0, s. 21, for “licence” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `3. Ins. b y s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “ goods” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “sub - sect ion ( 3 ) of section 11” (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 2010).`
